    <TABLE><TR>
    <TD WIDTH="100%">
        <A HREF="https://healpix.jpl.nasa.gov">HEALPix</A> by GÃ³rski et al. (2005) is de-facto standard for Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB) data storage and analysis, and is widely used in current and upcoming CMB experiments. Almost all the datasets in Legacy Archive for Microwave Background Data Analysis (<A HREF="https://lambda.gsfc.nasa.gov">LAMBDA</A>) use HEALPix as a format of choice. HEALPix Viewer is a macOS application which takes full advantage of GPU acceleration to visualize extremely large datasets in real time.

